manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The NH-L9i-17xx chromax.black is an all-black version of Noctua’s award-winning NH-L9i-17xx low-profile quiet CPU cooler for Intel LGA1700 (LGA17xx family) based HTPCs and Small Form Factor (SFF) builds. Thanks to the same proven heatsink design and NF-A9x14 PWM fan, it stays true to the NH-L9i-17xx’s successful formula of fusing a height of only 37mm with strong performance and excellent quietness of operation, as well as 100% RAM and PCIe compatibility. At the same time, the chromax.black version with its black fan and black coated heatsink combines these assets with a sleek stealth look. Topped off with the renowned SecuFirm2 low-profile mounting system for Intel LGA1700 (LGA17xx family) and Noctua’s enthusiast-grade NT-H1 thermal compound, the NH-L9i-17xx chromax.black is a premium choice for customers who seek an ultra-compact heatsink that looks just as great as it cools.

37mm low profile Due to the slim 23mm heatsink and the NF-A9x14 low profile fan that measures only 14mm in thickness, the NH-L9 stands a mere 37mm tall, which makes it ideal for use in compact HTPCs or Small Form Factor cases that offer minimum clearance for CPU coolers. 100% RAM compatibility The NH-L9i has a 95x95mm footprint that complies exactly with the Intel LGA1700 (LGA17xx family) socket keep-out zone. This means that it won't cause issues with VRM heatsinks and doesn't overhang the RAM slots, so it's fully compatible with tall memory modules. 100% compatibility with PCIe cards on mini-ITX Some mini-ITX motherboards have the PCIe slot sitting close to the 95x95mm socket zone. While larger coolers that exceed this zone are likely to block the PCIe slot, the 95x95mm sized NH-L9i provides full compatibility with PCIe cards. New revision for Intel’s LGA1700 (LGA17xx family) socket Since the original NH-L9i for LGA1200 and LGA115x has received more than 200 awards and recommendations from international hardware websites and magazines, the new 17xx revision builds on the same proven heatsink design to provide excellent low-profile cooling performance for LGA1700 CPUs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An absolute must for your Small Form-Factor(SFF) PC Builds!
reviews.reviewText: My AIO was not working as well as it should have, and I needed a fast solution since my idle temperatures kept climbing relentlessly... nearly 85°C! To avoid long term damage to the other components, I replaced my NZXT H1 v1 small form factor(SFF) rig's OEM AIO Cooler/Fan completely, and solely used the NOCTUA NH-L9i-17xx chromax.black instead. The difference was immediate, and the temperatures easily are in the high 30°C to low 40°C range when idle. I am thoroughly impressed with the quieter fan as well. Excellent product, that I can highly recommend to other users.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars its easy to install if you had one more hand.
reviews.reviewText: it is a very easy system to install. I put this on my z690i and it fit perfectly into that small space. Theres no wiggle room so it will hit around the inside of the vrams and m.2 areas unless you go literally straight down. the easy part is putting the 4 screws into the back of the motherboard but when you're trying to put on the cooler, having just a single extra hand will help because you can have that person hold the cooler and motherboard while you screw in the 4 screws.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great cooler for my NAS
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my 13100 that is setup to be a NAS it mounts quicker and easier than the stock intel cooler. Also it is cooler and quieter than the intel cooler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not sure if it's "because Boomer", but it sounds quiet to me.
reviews.reviewText: My CPU temps are sitting around 80 degrees F. (but I just browse YouTube)I can barely hear the fan if it runs at the 2500 rpm max, currently 1200 rpmish and almost silent.Everything fits in an AsRock DeskMeet B660 case.I5-12400 (no video card as yet)32 GB of RAM1TB of NVME.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for LGA170 CPU
reviews.reviewText: Simple "no brainier" four screw installation on LGA170 CPU with no ram interference. Super quiet and perfect addition to my be-quiet case. Perfect for any business performance application. If you like efficient silence, this is the one to get.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Don't use for powerful CPUs.
reviews.reviewText: It's a nice cooler and it fits in very neatly.I stupidly went for a low profile cooler because I wanted my motherboard to look nice through the glass case.I have this thing next to high performance memory and on a ASUS ROG Strix mobo.It COOKS. I have idle temps at around 35 C, but it'll shoot up to 70-80 C when playing a game or something.I honestly just thought a big Hyper 212 style cooler was going to be overkill since I didn't plan on overclocking. Hopefully I'll be able to return this and trade up for a water cooled system.Literally this thing is at the same level as my motherboard heatsinks.So between the small amount of heatsink material since it's low profile and my graphics card churning out heat at max load, this cooler really struggles to dissipate any significant amount of heat.Installation is pretty easy but it could've either done with better instructions or a more robust mounting system.I think this cooler would be great for perhaps a firewall or NAS, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Be careful with thermals on k chips
reviews.reviewText: I used this on a 12600k mini itx build. Was hitting 85/90 degrees celcius stock in cinebench (I did not let testing resume when it hit 90). Was also hitting 85 degrees in some cpu intensive games...Rather than purchasing a new cooler I disabled e-cores and undervolted by 50 millivolts...my temps are way better. With cinebench I still hit 80 degrees but in games it generally runs 60-65 degrees which is very appropriate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars one of the best coolers

reviews.reviewText: Fácil de instalar, silencioso e lindo demais.

This cooler is really nice. The mounting is kinda weird tho... From the back of the motherboard. But I do understand why, they just wanted the cooling capacity to be the best. But I also recommend to have the (anti bend) bracket for lga 1700 cpus. To get more cooling performance from this cooler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Noctua did well with this, always check BIOS for fan curve and set correctly for your own use, if not you'll likely whinge about it.Overall a solid Noctua product.
This is managing to keep my i5 12600K cool enough ( 70 ish c ) in a mini itx case.
